In a Bazaar India exclusive, heiress, activist, and entrepreneur Paris Hilton (@parishilton) has an intimate conversation with Bazaar India Editor Nandini Bhalla (@nandinibhalla) about her evolved views on life, social media, love, and the launch of her latest perfume, Ruby Rush by @parishiltonfragrances… 

Nandini Bhalla: You are famous for the catchphrase, ‘That’s hot’... What does ‘hot’ mean to you now? 
Paris Hilton: “‘Hot’, to me, is different from what it meant when I was younger. Today, I think legislation is ‘hot’—all the things that I’m doing on Capitol Hill in Washington DC, standing up for other people, making a difference and impact in the world, and really just carrying on my family’s legacy of philanthropic work... I think that’s what’s ‘hot’."

NB: And there’s a new term that you’ve come up with—sliving... Tell us more about that.
PH: “Sliving is a movement and a lifestyle. And it’s a word that I invented, which is basically ‘slaying’ and ‘living your best life’.”

NB: What is the one thing that people tend to get wrong about Paris?
PH: “That I’m a dumb blonde. I’m not. I’m just very good at pretending to be one.”

@ParisHilton is reclaiming her narrative, ushering in a new chapter to her life. Harper’s Bazaar Arabia’s March 2023 cover star and the ultimate Queen of Y2K style has recently been giving everyone a dose of throwback noughties glamour, all the while showing us who the real Paris is –  and the struggles she's been through to get to her new found place of strength. 

Born into the most famous hotel dynasty of all, her circumstances were certainly privileged – but despite decades of the media perpetuating the trope of heir-head bimbo, famous for being famous, it is Paris’ memoir – set for release on March 14 – that will inevitably show that while icons can perhaps be born, they need to be forged in the fire to truly be made. 
 
As she recontextualises the persona she carefully crafted during some of her darkest days, through the lens of trauma she experienced whilst attending boarding schools for troubled youth, the heiress-turned-multi-hyphenated entrepreneur, DJ and, now, new mother shares an entirely different side of herself with Bazaar Arabia: Paris Hilton, The Activist. @ParisHilton’s harrowing, abusive experiences at a series of boarding schools for troubled teens in the ‘90s has roused her advocacy and commitment to shutting them down. The Harper’s Bazaar Arabia’s March 2023 cover star has helped pass seven state laws to protect children in similar facilities, pushing for federal reform. As we went to press, she was visiting the White House with her mum, Kathy, pushing further forward her goal of ending this kind of child abuse forever.

“In the past few years, since my documentary… I've really been on this journey of self-discovery and learning so much about myself and how so much of it is trauma responses to what happened when I was a teenager,” she shares, speaking about how her famed persona was shaped by her time at Provo Canyon School in Utah. “It’s been extremely healing, putting it all out there.” In her new book, “Paris: The Memoir,” she writes candidly about how she suffered unimaginable physical, mental and sexual abuse at the hands of the staff. Let's start with my 10-minute @TikTok with @Hilton. Such an amazing piece of work created by my team at @11.11Media, @TBWAChiatNY, and Hilton’s team. @Influential helped us curate an amazing cast of culture-making TikTok creators and of course me, the OG influencer. Together we created magic and broke the convention of short, often-forgettable, brand videos. Next up is my statement collection, part of my “I Am” campaign, which my team created with the brilliant minds at @Ogilvy. We wanted to empower every person out there to embrace their true selves! The collection and campaign are a love letter to authenticity and self-expression and I'm over the moon that it resonated with so many of you. You're all amazing just the way you are! 🌟#ThisIsWhoIAm 

And my iconic collaboration with @Klarna, a massive global campaign across OOH, social, TV & my House of Y2K experiential event — the brand’s best-performing of all time! I loved the short film so much, which transported the audience to a world of dreams and wonder, brought to life by the talented @TanuMuino. It's a whimsical journey that shows how shopping can be a fun and easy experience. 🛍️ #ThatsSmoooth

Last but certainly not least, I'm thrilled to be recognized for my epic partnership with @LOrealParis and @UrbanDecay in @Roblox. Together, we dreamt up an immersive Halloween experience that featured digital costumes, DJ sets, and celebrity cameos. We brought makeup to the Metaverse in a digital wonderland, where beauty meets technology in the most glamorous way. 

Being nominated for these awards is a true honor and I'm so grateful for the recognition. Thank you all for being a part of this incredible journey! Stay tuned for more magic coming your way! 💖#Sliving 😍
